<title>Daniel Levitin: How to stay calm when you know you&#39;ll be stressed | TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript | TED</title>
<meta name="description" content="TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript: You&#39;re not at your best when you&#39;re stressed. In fact, your brain has evolved over millennia to release cortisol in stressful situations, inhibiting rational, logical thinking but potentially helping you survive, say, being attacked by a lion. Neuroscientist Daniel Levitin thinks there&#39;s a way to avoid making critical mistakes in stressful situations, when your thinking becomes clouded -- the pre-mortem. &quot;We all are going to fail now and then,&quot; he says. &quot;The idea is to think ahead to what those failures might be.&quot;" />
